						<p><b>Vietnamese Tet</b></p>

						<p>The Vietnamese word for New Year is
							<em>Tet</em>. It is celebrated for a full week, usually around the end of January or the beginning of February. To prepare for this important celebration, Vietnamese families clean their homes and even re-paint them, and buy new clothes. They celebrate with fireworks, loud gongs and music, gifts, and prayer.
						</p>
