						<p><b>Japanese New Year</b></p>

						<p>In Japan too, New Year or
							<em>Shogatsu</em>, is a major holiday. The night before, people go to the temple to worship and pray that the following year will be happy and prosperous. Special food that has been prepared in advance is used for the main meal. On New Year’s morning, people go to the houses of family members and friends to celebrate and exchange gifts.
						</p>
