						<p><b>Islamic New Year</b></p>

						<p>In most Islamic countries, the New Year celebration (called Al-Hijra) is much more low-key. Muslims do not celebrate the New Year much. However, they might mark it by setting some New Year Resolutions for themselves. This does vary by region though; for example, in Egypt, New Year is far more festive and loud!</p>
