						<p><b>Austrian New Year</b></p>

						<p>New Year in Austria is called
							<em>Sylvesterabend</em>. It is named after Saint Sylvester. According to myths, he slew an enormous dragon. At this time of the year, people celebrate with champagne toasts, decorations in homes, and confetti at parties. They go to church at midnight to give thanks and pray. Large cities also have a fireworks display and a major concert.
						</p>
